ðŸ”¹ Date Picker Inputs
html
Copy code
<input type="text" id="startDate" class="form-control datepicker" placeholder="Select Start Date">
<input type="text" id="endDate" class="form-control datepicker mt-2" placeholder="Select End Date">
ðŸ”¹ JavaScript:
javascript
Copy code
$(document).ready(function () {
    let today = new Date();

    $("#startDate").datepicker({
        format: "yyyy-mm-dd",
        autoclose: true,
        startDate: today // Disable past dates
    }).on("changeDate", function (e) {
        let startDate = e.format("yyyy-mm-dd");
        $("#endDate").datepicker("setStartDate", startDate);
    });

    $("#endDate").datepicker({
        format: "yyyy-mm-dd",
        autoclose: true
    }).on("changeDate", function (e) {
        let endDate = e.format("yyyy-mm-dd");
        $("#startDate").datepicker("setEndDate", endDate);
    });
});
ðŸŽ¯ Final Outcome
ðŸ”¹ Solution 1 (HTML5 Date Input) â†’ Simple, no extra libraries.
ðŸ”¹ Solution 2 (Bootstrap Datepicker) â†’ More user-friendly UI.

Now, when you select a start date, only valid future dates can be selected as the end date and vice versa. ðŸš€ Let me know if you need any modifications!







